content.description: Tipsy start, thin crack and short face climbing are highlighted in this beauty.  If in the area, a must-do.
content.location: Four feet right of the route Library Card.

content.description: Solid rock with friendly crack that never wields any crux.
content.location: North side of peak.  Route faces Shea Blvd.  If you have illegally parked off 142nd Street you will be able to see the route.

content.description: This is the place to visit after you are bored with the myriad of other classic destinations Arizona has to offer.  Better than Cochise, better than Sedona, better than Granite Mountain, better than the Superstitions.  Even better than Camelback and Lookout Mountain!  Could it be the best in Arizona...Always sunny, swarming with activity (bee's that is), lots of crumbly rock.  This unnamed peak saw activity in the 1970's.  We went out to repeat the original routes (Old Shakey and Library Route).  We located the routes along with a dangerous amount of very active bee hives on both climbs.  Wear a bee suit or climb on a snowy day to avoid death by a million angry bee's.
